{
  "doc_id": "37434",
  "text": "Dickkopf-1 (DKK1) is a negative regulator of the Wnt/β-catenin signaling pathway, which has a significant role in a variety of cellular processes, including differentiation, proliferation, cell motility and apoptosis [CITATION_1] . Increased DKK1 expression levels have been identified in patients with Wilms' tumors, hepatoblastoma, multiple myeloma and breast cancer, suggesting a potential role for DKK1 in carcinogenesis [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Studies have reported that the expression and roles of DKK1 differ between types of cancer, and that increased expression of DKK1 is common amongst numerous malignant tumors, including breast and lung cancer, as well as esophageal carcinomas [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , supporting the hypothesis for a potential oncogenic function of DKK1 [CITATION_6] .",
